features: ULTIMATE SCRATCH & IMPACT PROTECTION - With 3X shatter protection vs. an unprotected screen, tempered glass & reinforced edges to prevent chips & cracks, InvisibleShield Glass plus features Ion Matrix Technology for defense against drops, dings and scratches

ULTIMATE SCRATCH RESISTANCE - Featuring a precision surface finishing process, the screen protector provides maximum scratch resistance even if you accidentally put your phone in your pocket with the keys

CLEAN, SMUDGE-FREE SCREEN - The oil-resistant surface hides the visibility of fingerprints on your screen and does not interfere with your phone's touch sensitivity. Compatible with iPhone 13 and 13 Pro

STURDY DESIGN - With reinforced edges, it protects the vulnerable corners and edges of your screen from chips and stops cracks from starting and spreading. The surface is extremely seamless so that it feels like your phone's original screen
HASSLE-FREE INSTALLATION - Unlike most screen protectors, InvisbleShield Glass plus is easy to install. The EZ Apply installation with tray and tabs make installation seamless and bubble free
body.description: With the innovative Ion Matrix Technology to improve strength and protection, InvisibleShield Glass+ Screen Protection provides 3 times the shatter protection compared to an unprotected screen. It is scratch-resistant and features reinforced edges to protect your Apple iPhone 13 and 13 Pro. The near perfect surface finish makes the screen feel like new, while the reinforced edges protects the corners and edges of the device from chips and cracks. The oil reststant surface of the tempered glass prevents fingerprint marks, smudges and stains, and does not affect your phone's touch sensitivity. The EZ Apply installation with installation tray and high-quality adhesive allows you to apply the screen protector on your cell phone accurately without any bubbles. Glass+ has a limited lifetime warranty with replacement for damaged or worn products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wow what a difference
reviews.reviewText: Wow what a difference between the cheap knock offs and this one. I've never used anything but the $6-$15 screen protectors before and they did ok I guess except my screen would end up cracked. I got the iPhone 13 pro a month or two ago End it as always put a $12 screen protector on it. Well dropped it couple times an it was cracked so I took it off and the screen was crack to the phone so it is still under warranty and as everybody knows that apples warranty means "we will just give you a old refurbished phone for your brand new or only charge you 80% of what you paid for the phone (and that's with Apple care). So I broke down and convinced my wife to let me try one a little more expensive with a trusted name, as hesitant as she was she said ok and we reviewed many we ordered this to one and from the minute I opened the package it was great. They have a video with step by step instructions (I'm sure everyone does now) the alignment tabs are GREAT.??I normally go through three just putting it on without dust under it or bubbles then have To take it off three or four times then it won't stick so then I have to use another one. Cleaned the phone, dusted, followed the instructions and wow what a difference. It adhered on it own damn near and not one bubble. The clarity is damn near perfect , no smudging and it feels like it's part of the phone. Excellent Product Zagg. And I more than happy to pay for shipping for a free replacment if or when needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Have had this for about a month and it is doing a good job of protecting my screen. One thing I particularly like about it is that is doesn't show smears on the screen from your fingers--not nearly as much as previous film screen protectors I've used. A minor complaint is that it does seem to collect lint, or fine particles of fabric, from being carried in a pocket and this is more noticeable than I've seen with other screen protectors.I did have one tiny trapped bubble, or dust speck, after applying the screen protector, which was annoying, but it was very small and in an area where it isn't very noticeable and I don't "see" it anymore. Didn't think it was worth trying to get a replacement from the company, but, due to the fairly high price tag for these protectors, maybe I should have!I would recommend these screen protectors, though would recommend getting them on sale. I also know someone whose phone was dropped when they fell down some stairs. The screen protector was cracked in multiple places but the screen on the phone was fine, so that is another big selling point for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Doesn’t actually fit
reviews.reviewText: I am so mad about this screen protector. Before I installed it I watched the video twice, and I made sure to follow all the instructions exactly. I used the plastic installation kit and with using that, the placement of the protector ends up so that it covers half of the black box at the top of the screen where the camera is. I didn’t think much about it though because it’s made by Zagg, and surely they know what their doing. Their products are supposed to be superior to all other brands. Turns out that’s a load of crap. I had family in town to see me because I’m going through treatment for advanced stage 4 cancer, and last night I used the front facing camera to take a picture with my nieces. The picture was awful quality, it was blurry, and looked like we were in really poor lighting. We tried several different places but they all turned out the same. I’ve only had the phone for 3 days so I was going to return it because I thought it was an iPhone issue. This afternoon it occurred to me that it might be because of the screen protector. I took it off and took a “selfie” and the picture turned out great. Too bad my nieces went back home early this morning and won’t be back for another year. I will say that the feel of the screen protector was great, and I especially loved that it didn’t show any finger prints or smudges. If you buy it, don’t use the plastic thing that comes with it and make sure to install it so that it’s low on the screen. As in, the very, VERY bottom of the screen. I’m surprised such a well known company would let this pass as acceptable.
